# findString.py
Python script that looks for a specific string in Cisco Configuration Files and returns all sections that contain it.

The scripts takes a path to a directory or it runs in the current directory if not directory was provided (default) and searches all Cisco Config files for a specifi string. If it finds the string, it writes out the whole elemnt, not just the line.  

Usage: findString.py -s < Search String > [-d] < Search Directory > [-c] < String >\n"  
    -s, --searchString      The string to search for. This is required."  
    -d, --searchDirectory   The location of the files that are searched, by default, current directory."  
    -c, --contains          Only files that contain the provided string will be searched.\n"  
